Alert SA-AFUN-03 (Gste)#

This alert reports selection signals on Chromosome 2RL within the region 76,329,285-76,586,750 bp.

Selection signals#

Selection signals overlapping this genome region are shown in the figure below.

Cohorts affected#

Overlapping selection signals are found in the following cohorts.

  • Benin / Ouidah / funestus / 2014 / Q2

  • Democratic Republic of the Congo / Kinshasa / funestus / 2015 / Q2

  • Ghana / Adansi Akrofuom / funestus / 2014 / Q1

  • Nigeria / Remo North / funestus / 2015 / Q1

Insecticide resistance genes#

The following genes are found within this genome region and may be driving recent positive selection based on evidence for an association with insecticide resistance. Please note that other genes are also within the affected genome region and may be driving selection.

LOC125763977 (Gste2, AFUN2_012779, AFUN015809)#

This gene encodes a glutathione S-transferase enzyme. Variants in this gene have been associated with DDT and pyrethroid insecticide resistance in Anopheles funestus. See also:

  • Riveron et al. (2014) A single mutation in the GSTe2 gene allows tracking of metabolically based insecticide resistance in a major malaria vector

  • Tchouaki et al. (2019) A marker of glutathione S-transferase-mediated resistance to insecticides is associated with higher Plasmodium infection in the African malaria vector Anopheles funestus

  • Kouamo et al. (2021) Genome-Wide Transcriptional Analysis and Functional Validation Linked a Cluster of Epsilon Glutathione S-Transferases with Insecticide Resistance in the Major Malaria Vector Anopheles funestus across Africa

See also#

  • Anopheles gambiae complex selection alert SA-AGAM-06.
